<font face="Serif" size="18">The real gift is to be ungifted,</font>

322
00:17:48,359 --> 00:17:50,695
<font face="Serif" size="18">and from what I saw
in your <i>Green Arrow</i></font><font face="Serif" size="18"> spec script,</font>

323
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:52,363
<font face="Serif" size="18">that's the gift you were given.</font>

324
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:55,825
<font face="Serif" size="18">- You couldn't have seen that.
- I'm Joseph Campbell. I saw it.</font>

325
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:58,536
<font face="Serif" size="18">- The villain was a placeholder.
- I said I saw it, Jan.</font>

326
00:17:58,619 --> 00:18:02,081
<font face="Serif" size="18">I didn't say I could get past page five.
Your villains aren't the problem.</font>

327
00:18:02,164 --> 00:18:07,378
<font face="Serif" size="18">The problem is, when you write, you're a villain.
If you want to be a hero, just stop.</font>

328
00:18:07,461 --> 00:18:08,421
<font face="Serif" size="18">[sobbing]</font>

329
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:16,387
<font face="Serif" size="18">You know what? Maybe I will register.</font>

330
00:18:17,305 --> 00:18:20,141
<font face="Serif" size="18">Say it. Tell me I'm the new Mr. Nimbus.</font>

331
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:26,063
<font face="Serif" size="18">- Oh, looks like your writer took a hiatus.
- Oh, fuck.</font>

332
00:18:26,147 --> 00:18:28,774
<font face="Serif" size="18">You're less motivated to fight now,
so this is punching down,</font>

333
00:18:28,858 --> 00:18:30,276
<font face="Serif" size="18">but you've got it coming.</font>

334
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:38,159
<font face="Serif" size="18">Please, let me live. I promise to be cooler.
I'll be less inside baseball.</font>

335
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:39,535
<font face="Serif" size="18">Maybe I change my name?</font>

336
00:18:42,163 --> 00:18:46,626
<font face="Serif" size="18">- You failed me.
- No, I failed you.</font>

337
00:18:46,709 --> 00:18:47,918
<font face="Serif" size="18">[coughing]</font>

338
00:18:48,002 --> 00:18:51,714
<font face="Serif" size="18">All good things must come to an end.</font>

339
00:18:51,797 --> 00:18:54,592
<font face="Serif" size="18">All bad things too, though,
so don't flatter yourself.</font>

340
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:57,595
<font face="Serif" size="18">Jan, Joseph Campbell says you have
to be the one to put him down.</font>

341
00:18:57,678 --> 00:18:59,847
<font face="Serif" size="18">Wait, wait, Joseph Campbell also says,</font>

342
00:18:59,930 --> 00:19:02,767
<font face="Serif" size="18">you have to use
this brand-new limited edition Rick plush,</font>

343
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:07,146
<font face="Serif" size="18">available only on rick-plush.biz.
Supplies are limited. Act now.</font>

344
00:19:07,229 --> 00:19:08,105
<font face="Serif" size="18">He did?</font>

345
00:19:08,856 --> 00:19:10,650
<font face="Serif" size="18">- [grunting]
- [doll squeaking]</font>

346
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:14,987
<font face="Serif" size="18">Shh...</font>

347
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:24,914
<font face="Serif" size="18">- That's the last time I buy a toy from a Rick.
- The plushies are obviously well-made.</font>

348
00:19:30,753 --> 00:19:34,757
<font face="Serif" size="18">- Thanks for getting us back alive, Rick.
- Well, I am a master of both worlds, Morty.</font>

349
00:19:37,218 --> 00:19:41,138
<font face="Serif" size="18">Joseph Campbell told me to stop writing.
Because it should be effortless.</font>

350
00:19:41,222 --> 00:19:43,808
<font face="Serif" size="18">And when it happens organically,
that's when it's meant to be.</font>

351
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:47,978
<font face="Serif" size="18">You know, like me. I'm a writer, here's a pencil.
Writers use pencils.</font>

352
00:19:48,062 --> 00:19:51,565
<font face="Serif" size="18">Okay, so, like, what if, like, a pencil used me?
Like, okay. Yeah!</font>

353
00:19:51,649 --> 00:19:55,236
<font face="Serif" size="18">Okay, so it's like a magic pencil
that writes the writer's life.</font>

354
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:59,907
<font face="Serif" size="18">Holy shit, it's a movie about a writer!
I am back!</font>

355
00:20:01,283 --> 00:20:02,493
<font face="Serif" size="18">[theme music playing]</font>

356
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:36,861
<font face="Serif" size="18">Yeah, I'm Tag-Man! I live in the tag!</font>

357
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:42,324
<font face="Serif" size="18">I am the tag! I'm Tag-Man!
Tag, tag of the episode man!</font>

358
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:45,619
<font face="Serif" size="18">"Did you get any of that?" When the, yeah,
when an episode's over, look out,</font>

359
00:20:45,703 --> 00:20:47,663
<font face="Serif" size="18">because, yeah, here comes Tag-Man!</font>

360
00:20:47,747 --> 00:20:52,960
<font face="Serif" size="18">And I'm crazy! Tag-Man! Yeah!
I'ma tag your ass!</font>

361
00:20:53,043 --> 00:20:59,175
<font face="Serif" size="18">Tag that ass. Tag-Ass-Man! I'm an Ass-Man now!
I'm a Tag-Man!</font>

362
00:20:59,258 --> 00:21:02,261
<font face="Serif" size="18">Here's what you get. Here's your tag!
Yeah, you want some more?</font>

363
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:06,557
<font face="Serif" size="18">You want-- You want some more tag,
you sick piece of shit? Because I'm Tag-Man!</font>

364
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:12,980
<font face="Serif" size="18">I miss my wife. Too bad. This is it.
Tag-Man, yeah!</font>

